Note: HIR Type System Types (13000-13999)
Note:
Task #448: HIR_GENERIC_TYPE (13001) and HIR_FUNCTION_TYPE (13004) are
also defined in hir_nodes.runa as value-identical aliases for the
translation node-kind space, following the #433 aliasing precedent
(HIR_LITERAL/HIR_IDENTIFIER). This is load-bearing: the bootstrap
import system flattens namespaces, merge_imported_globals skips an
imported global whose name already exists in the consuming program's
table, and codegen inlines an immutable integer constant from the
first matching table entry. So for same-name constants the winning
value is the first definition in preorder depth-first import traversal
(own file first, then imports in source order), regardless of which
module alias the qualified read names. Divergent values across the two
files produce silent cross-object kind mismatches. If either value
changes, change BOTH files.
:End Note
Constant HIR_BASIC_TYPE as Integer is 13000          Note: Primitive type (Integer, Float, String, Boolean, etc.)
Constant HIR_GENERIC_TYPE as Integer is 13001        Note: Generic type with resolved parameters
Constant HIR_UNION_TYPE as Integer is 13002          Note: Union type (A OR B)
Constant HIR_INTERSECTION_TYPE as Integer is 13003   Note: Intersection type (A AND B)
Constant HIR_FUNCTION_TYPE as Integer is 13004       Note: Function type signature
Constant HIR_OPTIONAL_TYPE as Integer is 13005       Note: Optional type (T?)
Constant HIR_ARRAY_TYPE as Integer is 13006          Note: Array type with element type
Constant HIR_TUPLE_TYPE as Integer is 13007          Note: Tuple type with element types
Constant HIR_RECORD_TYPE as Integer is 13008         Note: Record type with field types
Constant HIR_TYPE_PARAMETER as Integer is 13009      Note: Generic type parameter
Constant HIR_TYPE_CONSTRAINT as Integer is 13010     Note: Type constraint (T: Trait)
Constant HIR_REFERENCE_TYPE as Integer is 13011      Note: Reference type (&T, &mut T)
Constant HIR_POINTER_TYPE as Integer is 13012        Note: Raw pointer type (*T)
Constant HIR_SLICE_TYPE as Integer is 13013          Note: Slice type ([T])
Constant HIR_NEVER_TYPE as Integer is 13014          Note: Never type (!)
Constant TYPE_INTEGER as Integer is 13015            Note: Resolved primitive Integer type kind (band extension 2026-06-09: specific primitive kinds so HIRTypeInfo.type_kind distinguishes Integer/Float/String/Boolean without re-reading type_name)
Constant TYPE_FLOAT as Integer is 13016              Note: Resolved primitive Float type kind
Constant TYPE_STRING as Integer is 13017             Note: Resolved primitive String type kind
Constant TYPE_BOOLEAN as Integer is 13018            Note: Resolved primitive Boolean type kind
Constant HIR_ENUM_TYPE as Integer is 13019           Note: Enum/variant type kind (variants stored in field_types list)

